Assignment 1.05: Player Character and Monsters
Thomas Powell

This file will print a dungeon with monsters. One can move with the 1-9 keys or
    the vim keys. Use q to quit. Use m to open the monster list, up and down arrow
    keys to scroll through the list. Use the ESC key to exit the monster list.
    The monster list shows the locations relative to the player.
Use "make rlg327" to compile executable dungeon.

Use "./rlg327" to generate a random dungeon.

Use "./rlg327 --save" to save dungeon to /home/"insert_username_here"/.rlg327/dungeon

Use "./rlg327 --load" to load dungeon from same location.

Use "./rlg327 --nummon x" to generate a dungeon with 'x' amount of monsters

Use "make clean" to delete the generated files.